The implementation in `bb004_mdtable/normalizer.py`:
- Detects a pipe table as a header line followed by a separator line (cells matching `:?-+:?`)
- Splits rows by `|`, strips cell contents (so padding is removed on re-parse → idempotent)
- Computes per-column width as the max content width across all rows
- Normalizes the separator row to `---` per column
